Movie: Once Upon a Time in America

Review: What can I say, I love Shelley Duvall and I love the campy, nostalgic art direction in this. It’s definitely something that I’m sad I missed during my childhood, I know I would have absolutely loved it. Also, can we talk about the amount of effort put into this, down to the spinning teacups in the kitchen and the costumes matching the set decorations? The dream would be to work on something as whimsical as this.
Expect an excessive amount of heavy metal, maggots, and a pimpin’ chimp. 🤘 If I could give this movie a zodiac sign it’d be Scorpio.

Review: Makes you feel the innocence and wonder of childhood and then hits you with harsh adult realities. Shot very much like a documentary, (aside from Willem Dafoe’s appearance) we’re given a window into a child’s world and are reminded of a simpler time where one’s imagination is heightened and reality just isn’t important. As viewers, we can pinpoint many of Moonee’s daily activities as wrong... but to her, the world is still very much a magical realm, where forks should…
